The paper discusses security issues in cooperative intelligent transportation systems (cITS), which involves wireless communication between vehicles and infrastructure. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of misbehavior detection mechanisms, which involves analyzing information semantics to detect attacks, which aligns with the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The cITS ecosystem is highly dynamic and heterogeneously managed, which requires the use of system-level approaches to ensure safety and efficiency, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the classification and analysis of research papers on the topic, which involves data analysis and organization, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
